parameters.content:
### Core Trigger Nodes
- **Manual Trigger**: Test and debug your workflows during development
- **Cron**: Schedule workflows to run at specific times (daily reports, weekly checks)
- **App event**: Start workflows from external events

### Universal Data Processing
- **Split**: Flatten a data structure
- **Aggregate**: Merge a data structure (nest)
- **Set**: Create and modify data fields - the most versatile node
- **IF**: Add decision-making logic to route information differently
- **Code**: Custom manipulation for complex transformations

### Connectivity & APIs
- **HTTP Request**: Connect to any external API or service. GET, POST & Authentication
- **Webhook Response**: Send data back after processing

https://dummyjson.com/docs/products

### Storage Solutions
- **Google Sheets**: Perfect for lightweight data storage and reporting
- **Database nodes**: Connect to MySQL, Airtable, Notion, etc.

### AI Integration
- **LLM Node**: Bring AI intelligence into your workflows
- **When judgement is required**: [if this then that] -> traditional deterministic logic fails. Traditional nodes work perfectly for "if invoice > $1000, send to approval" but fall short with "if customer email suggests they might cancel, flag for retention".
- **AI Agent**: Only when something MORE is required (tools, memory, data access, thorough thinking)
# 13 NODES TO ---- TO MASTER THE 80/20 OF N8N

parameters.content:
### Conventions
- **Flow direction and order**: Left to right, top to bottom
- **Sequential Execution**: By default, n8n executes nodes synchronously (one after another, not in parallel)
- **Node runs**: Nodes will run once PER INPUT. 5 inputs, 5 runs.
- **Branching**: Workflows can split into multiple paths using conditional nodes (like If nodes)
- **Active**: If you want anything external to run -> activate the flow
